<kml>

<concept name=Be-Closed><system-documentation name=Be-Closed>

<superconcept name=Be-Blocked>

<definition>

  The <conceptref name=Portal> through a <conceptref name=Barrier> is
  closed, preventing movement through the Portal.  A Portal is put into this 
  state by <conceptref name=Close> and taken out of the state by
  <conceptref name=Open>.

</definition>

<requiredslotlist>

   <slotdescription name=object>
      the <conceptref name=Portal> that is closed
   </slotdescription>

</requiredslotlist>

<examplesentencelist>

   <examplesentence>
     <text>The jar is closed.</text>
     <slotdescription name=object>the mouth of the jar</slotdescription>
   </examplesentence>
   <comment>
   The mouth of the jar plays the role of portal, and is therefore the object
   of the Be-Closed state.  In contrast, the jar lid plays the role of 
   <conceptref name=Portal-Covering> when the jar is closed.
   </comment>
   
</examplesentencelist>

<neighborlist>

   <neighbor name=Close>
      Close is the action that puts a portal in the state of Be-Closed.
   </neighbor>

</neighborlist>

</kml>


